Title: What discipline really means?
Desc: What discipline really means? 1 : to punish or penalize for the sake of enforcing obedience and perfecting moral character. 2 : to train or develop by instruction and exercise especially in self-control. 3a : to bring (a group) under control discipline troops. b : to impose order upon serious writers discipline and refine their writing styles.

Title: What are the 3 types of self-discipline?
Desc: Three types of Self-Discipline: Here are examples of three types: active discipline, reactive discipline, and proactive discipline.

Title: How do I become creative in frontend developer?
Desc: if you're planning to become a front end developer, you should add some creative sparkle to your knowledge base by integrating basic (digital) design skills.

Title: What is discipline example?
Desc: An example of discipline is a time out for a child who has just pushed his sibling. A state of order based on submission to authority. A set of rules regulating behaviour. A controlled behaviour; self-control.

Title: Is front end development Easy?
Desc: The practice of front end development is similar to playing the bass: it's easy to learn but difficult to master. There is a lot more to it than HTML and CSS (which are plenty difficult onto themselves).

Title: How is discipline a strength?
Desc: Because people with the strength of Discipline can plan, organize, structure and execute, they seem to be able to achieve this with great accuracy and productivity within structured environments. People with the strength of Discipline like to know what is expected of them.
